# Versioning (this repo)

Framework uses **SemVer** — [VERSION](../VERSION), [CHANGELOG.md](../CHANGELOG.md), rules: [VERSIONING.md](../VERSIONING.md).

## Before `git commit`

**Behaviour change** (scripts, skills, `INSTRUCTIONS.md`, hooks…):

1. `bash scripts/bump-version.sh {patch|minor|major} "one-line description"`
2. Stage `VERSION`, `CHANGELOG.md`, and touched files
3. Commit: `type: summary (vX.Y.Z)`

**Doc-only** (`README.md`, `docs/**`, `templates/**`) — no bump; commit as usual.

| Change type | Bump |
|-------------|------|
| Script/skill/protocol fix | `patch` |
| New skill / verify check | `minor` |
| Breaking protocol or schema | `major` + Migration in CHANGELOG |

Pre-commit enforces bump only for behaviour-changing paths. Emergency: `git commit --no-verify`.

## Do not version

- `$MEMORY_HOME` user data — never commit here
- Per-project `chats/projects/<slug>.md` — distill content, not framework SemVer
